DETERING ET AL. <::chart: The image displays two line graphs side-by-side, illustrating brain catecholamine concentrations (Dopamine and Norepinephrine) in a prenatal experimental group over time. Both graphs share the same x-axis, labeled "-4 -2 BIRTH 1 WEEK 2 WEEK 3 WEEK", representing time points relative to birth. The y-axis for both graphs is labeled "ng/g", indicating concentration. The graphs show three distinct lines, two solid and one dashed, each with error bars, representing different experimental conditions or groups. **Left Graph: DOPAMINE (Prenatal)** - The y-axis ranges from 100 to 800 ng/g. - All three lines show an increasing trend in dopamine concentration from -4 (prenatal) to 3 weeks post-birth. - At -4, concentrations are between 50-100 ng/g. - At BIRTH, concentrations are between 100-200 ng/g. - At 1 WEEK, concentrations are between 200-300 ng/g. - At 2 WEEK, concentrations are between 300-400 ng/g. - At 3 WEEK, concentrations range from approximately 500 ng/g (dashed line) to 750 ng/g (solid lines). **Right Graph: NOREPINEPHRINE (Prenatal)** - The y-axis ranges from 100 to 300 ng/g. - All three lines also show an increasing trend in norepinephrine concentration from -4 (prenatal) to 3 weeks post-birth. - At -4, concentrations are between 20-50 ng/g. - At BIRTH, concentrations are between 50-100 ng/g. - At 1 WEEK, concentrations are between 100-150 ng/g. - At 2 WEEK, concentrations are between 150-250 ng/g. - At 3 WEEK, concentrations range from approximately 200 ng/g (dashed line) to 300 ng/g (solid lines). Fig. 3a. Brain catecholamine concentration in the prenatal experimental group. For explanation of experimental conditions, symbols, and statistical significance, see Fig. 2.::> <::chart: Two line charts showing brain catecholamine concentration in the postnatal experimental group. **Chart 1: DOPAMINE (Postnatal)** - Y-axis: ng/g (ranging from 100 to 700) - X-axis: Time points (BIRTH, 1 WEEK, 2 WEEK, 3 WEEK) - Data Series 1 (Solid Line): - BIRTH: ~200 ng/g - 1 WEEK: ~130 ng/g - 2 WEEK: ~350 ng/g - 3 WEEK: ~620 ng/g - Data Series 2 (Dashed Line): - BIRTH: ~180 ng/g - 1 WEEK: ~140 ng/g - 2 WEEK: ~420 ng/g - 3 WEEK: ~550 ng/g **Chart 2: NOREPINEPHRINE (Postnatal)** - Y-axis: ng/g (ranging from 100 to 300) - X-axis: Time points (BIRTH, 1 WEEK, 2 WEEK, 3 WEEK) - Data Series 1 (Solid Line): - BIRTH: ~120 ng/g - 1 WEEK: ~70 ng/g - 2 WEEK: ~150 ng/g - 3 WEEK: ~210 ng/g - Data Series 2 (Dashed Line): - BIRTH: ~120 ng/g - 1 WEEK: ~70 ng/g - 2 WEEK: ~240 ng/g - 3 WEEK: ~280 ng/g : chart::> Fig. 3b. Brain catecholamine concentration in the postnatal experimental group. For explanation of experimental conditions, symbols, and statistical significance, see Fig. 2. 15
